parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate or no readings on the speedometer, temperature gauge, and fuel gauge, leading to safety risks such as accidents, overheating, or running out of fuel.
symptoms: The speedometer
temperature gauge
and fuel gauge may not work or display inaccurate readings
including sticking
jumping
or not resetting to zero.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause issues with the vehicle's lighting, including the driving lights, blinkers, and interior lights, which can increase the risk of accidents or reduce visibility.
symptoms: The driving lights
blinkers
and interior lights may not work or may malfunction
including burning out frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body control module can cause issues with the vehicle's interior systems, including the power windows, door locks, and remotes, which can increase the risk of accidents or reduce safety.
symptoms: The power windows
door locks
and remotes may not work or may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall or not start, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine may stall or not start
and the vehicle may experience delayed response when starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding door can cause injuries to passengers, especially children, as it may not stop or reverse when an obstacle is detected, leading to crushing or trapping of body parts.
symptoms: The power sliding door closes with various body parts in its path
does not stop or reverse when an obstacle is detected
requires excessive force to activate the auto-reverse safety feature
and may open or close by itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust on the rocker panels can weaken the integral body structure, leading to holes and compromising the overall safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: Rust on the rocker panels
weakened integral body structure
and holes formed in the body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding door can cause injuries to passengers, especially children, and potentially lead to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The power sliding door opens or closes unexpectedly
fails to stop when obstructed
requires excessive force to stop
or opens halfway and closes halfway
leaving the operator to manually open or close the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sensor Failure in Power Sliding Door
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sensor in the power sliding door can cause the door to close without stopping, even when someone is in between the door and the frame, leading to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: The power sliding door closes without stopping when obstructed
and the sensor fails to detect the presence of a person or object in the door's path.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent opening and closing of the power sliding door can cause safety issues, especially when the door opens or closes unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The power sliding door opens or closes intermittently
sometimes without warning
and may occur while the vehicle is in motion.
